my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Galley equipment to be well maintained and any leaks are promptly reported; 
b) Drainage channels and drip trays are provided where spills are likely; 
c) Spillages to be cleaned immediately and the deck left dry; 
d) There are no trailing cables or obstructions; 
e) Trip hazards are clearly marked; 
f) Make sure suitable footwear with a good grip is worn.

a) Cook to be trained on how to handle hot oils and how to safely use, empty and clean the fryer, were applicable; 
b) Use of appropriate PPE: long sleeve t-shirts, heat-resistant gloves, cloths and aprons;
c) 'Hot water' signs to be displayed at the sinks and 'hot surface' signs to be displayed at the hot plates; 
d) Make sure all pan-handles are in good condition; e) In adverse weather, guards should be fitted on the range to prevent hot pans / pots from falling.

a) Cook to be trained in the safe use, maintenance and storage of knives; 
b) Crew must only use suitable cutters for opening packages and must not use knives; 
c) Make sure all knife handles are in good condition; 
d) Knifes should not be left submerged in the wash basin, they should be washed immediately.

a) Wherever possible and sensible, the Cook should use tools (i.e. cutlery, tongs, scoops, etc) to handle food rather than their hands;
b) Where handling cannot be avoided, ensure hands are washed promptly after handling. 
c) Ensure the Cook thoroughly dries their hands after washing them;
d) The Cook must regularly check for dry, red or itchy skin on their hands; 
e) Smoking is strictly forbidden in the galley; 
f) The food store / fridge / freezers must be kept clean and at an adequate temperature.

a) The Cook is aware on how to use and store cleaning products safely, and never to transfer chemicals to an unmarked container; 
b) Mops, brushes and protective gloves to be provided and used; 
c) Protective gloves are to be rinsed after use and stored in a clean place.

a) Any defective equipment, plugs, discoloured sockets, damaged cables are promptly reported;
b) Any faulty equipment should be promptly taken out of use; 
c) All power-operated equipment must be disconnected from the mains prior to cleaning.
